\subsubsection{(G-7) Saturated Earth }
d240 2
a241 2
\emph{Range:} 100 feet (+50/Rank) \\
\emph{Duration:} 1 hour (+1/Rank) \\
d249 9
a257 1
The Adept summons water from deep within the earth, rising to the surface in 100 seconds (-5/Rank), causing the ground in an area of 100 feet (+10/Rank) radius to become totally sodden. Earth will turn to mud. Sand has a 30\% chance of turning into quicksand (swallowing any trapped individuals in 20 seconds), and a 70\% chance of turning into firm hard sand facilitating easy movement. The Adept may alter these chances by 1\% per Rank. Wetlands will be unaffected by this spell as will solid rocky terrain. With this spell all wells in an area can be caused to fill and all crops will be well watered.
d262 2
a263 2
\emph{Range:} 90 feet (+15/Rank) \\
\emph{Duration:} 5 days (+1/Rank) \\
d271 9
a279 1
This spell may be used to strengthen the structure of any ship or boat, repair leaks or holes, restep masts, etc. At Rank 10 and above, a small sail craft can be constructed out of available wood. At Rank 15 or above, a large craft (40 feet or more in length) may be constructed. At the end of the spells duration, its effects are undone; a constructed craft will fall apart (even in mid-ocean). In addition, any craft which is affected by this spell has its chance of encountering sea monsters, pirates or typhoons, decreased by 5\% (+1/Rank).
d284 2
a285 2
\emph{Range:} 15 feet (+15/Rank) \\
\emph{Duration:} 1 hour (+1/Rank) \\
d293 6
a298 1
The spell allows the Adept to communicate with any one form of aquatic life within range. This communication usually consists of both speech and gesture. All members of the selected generic type of aquatic that are within speaking range can be understood and can understand the Adept. The Adept may have more than one spell on at once, as long as they are for different generic types.
d300 1
a300 1
\subsubsection{(G-10) Summon Aquatic Life }
d308 1
a308 1
\emph{Storage:} Investment, Ward, Magical Trap \\
d312 4
a315 1
The Adept may summon 1 aquatic creature (+1/Rank). It may take up to 30 minutes (-30 seconds per Rank) for the aquatic life forms to arrive. The species must be native to the area to be summoned and the Adept must be within 100 feet of a body of water.
d317 1
a317 1
\subsubsection{(G-11) Water Breathing }
d321 1
a321 1
\emph{Duration:} 1 hour (+1/Rank) \\
d329 5
a333 1
The spell forms a set of gills in the subjects neck and covers their eyes with a transparent film. This allows the target to breath and see equally well under water as on land. The target may cast spells subject to the restrictions of their College. (The spell does not affect the targets ability to operate on the surface.)
d335 1
a335 1
\subsubsection{(G-12) Water Creation }
d347 4
a350 1
The Adept must touch the substance from which water is to be drawn. The spell allows the Adept to extract moisture from the air, or from plants (providing there is moisture available to be extracted) to the amount of 1 pint (+1/Rank).
